# Task Tracker Application

## Technology Used
- HTML
- CSS
- Javascript

## Features Completed
- Add task
- View task list
- Mark task as completed
- Delete task
- Show info for the number of tasks completed of total tasks

## How to Run
1. Download the project zip.
2. Extract the files.
3. Double click the html file to open it in browser.
4. Write text in the input area and press "Add Task" button to add a task to the list.
5. Click the checkbox to mark a task as completed.
6. Click the delete button to delete a task.

## Challenges Faced
1. Had to revise core HTML, CSS, Javascript because there were restrictions in using external packages and libraries from the internet.
2. Couldn't implement "clearing the text input area after add task button is pressed".
3. Had debugging issues even if one of the mistake was as small as "an extra 's' in a variable name"

## Improvements Planned
With the current tech stack:
1. More responsive css.
2. Dark mode and light mode toggle.
3. Use icons instead of buttons an enhanced UX.
4. Add date and time to a task.
5. Task structure containing 1 line title and detailed description in the form of steps, i.e., sub list in list items.
